I ordered breakfast here on Postmates. I had asked for tortillas and sour cream on the side with my Mexican chorizo skillet. When my order arrived it had a note on the box stating “no tortillas or sour cream, we are not a Mexican restaurant.” That’s fine I get it. But you don’t have to be rude and state that on the box. A simple “Sorry no sour cream or tortillas” would’ve sufficed. You’re not a Mexican restaurant, fine. But I received a Mexican skillet. Anyway that’s not even the main problem. I paid $25 for a bacon egg & cheese croissant and a Mexican chorizo skillet w a small coke. The croissant was soggy and cold from the styrofoam to go box and the hash brown it came with tasted freezer burn. The Mexican skillet was almost not edible. The eggs were like a plain sponge and I didn’t even receive napkins or a fork so I had to go and ask for one across the street. Overall not happy. DO NOT WASTE YOUR MONEY.

This is one the cosiest coffee shops I've ever been to.
